{
  "text": "The writing process is unique to each individual student; students bring their own individual characteristics, including linguistic and general literacy backgrounds, prior domain knowledge, as well as affective states (e.g., attitudes toward academic writing, engagement with the task), all of which potentially affect their performance (Gupta et al., 2022; Pineteh, 2014).",
